propriate loss optimization Identify emerging risk issues and initiate mitigating strategies Monitor effectiveness of implementation of risk strategies and policies Undertake a periodic review and assessment of the Bank\u2019s investment in risk management Maintain cost discipline Ensure that robust customer treatment processes are in place with regular reviews to ensure they are consistent, effective, efficient and best-in-class Strengthen the Bank\u2019s understanding of risk management, by incorporating risk considerations in all activities undertaken to enhance shareholder value Manage key relationships with regulators, rating agencies, industry bodies and auditors with respect to CBB Work effectively with Head of Consumer and Business Banking Build a strong cross functional Team Lead the CBB Risk People Agenda including succession planning, talent management, performance management and improving employee engagement. #LI-SB1 Qualifications Typical qualifications would include an undergraduate or post-graduate degree in Business Administration, Finance, Statistics or a related field. Experience 15+ Years of credit risk management experience Preferably retail banking or consumer lending risk experience Exposure to demanding operational environments to gain insight into the most effective risk management applications/strategies Working across all levels of the organization to understand cross-functional linkages and interdependencies, as well as the implications of credit risk at both a strategic level and at the business level Experience of creating, developing and leading a sizeable team A high level of professional competence which helps to determine solutions around appropriate fraud risk measures, risk processes, risk monitoring and management Skills Understands the strategies of the Bank and collaborates with the business to accomplish these strategies Ability to form effective relationships and achieve influence at the most senior level in the organization Demonstrated business knowledge, such as experience leading a P&L unit Communication and interpersonal skills, including the capacity to articulate the case for risk management in the language of business Established financial and accounting acumen Ability to make robust/tough decisions which may be contrary to the business wishes Understand and interpret complex business requirements Proven ability to prioritize competing demands Demonstrated ability to assess Risk trends, both internally and externally Strong leadership and management ability, developing and motivating employees Ability to drive change Developing and retaining critical talent and building an effective leadership team Job : Top Management Primary Location : Massachusetts-BOSTON-75 State Street - 06366 - State Street-Corp Organization : CRO (8855) Schedule : Full-time Job Posting : Apr 21, 2020, 12:15:20 PM ",
